<tr>
<td>1987</td>
<td>The Foundation notes the existence of <a href="/scp-4755">SCP-4755</a> but fails to determine its source or nature.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>01/13/1999</td>
<td>Death is contained as <a href="/scp-4260">SCP-4260</a> after voluntarily manifesting and requesting medical assistance.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>March 1999</td>
<td>First completion of Procedure 8917; SCP-4260 is terminated and reanimated.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>2003</td>
<td><a href="/apas">Apollyon</a> manifests for the first time and destroys Site-17, but is turned back by Dr. Skyler. Dr. Weathers is contracted as the Provisional Site Director.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>5/13/2005</td>
<td>Irantu <em>Mark-LXXII</em> contacts the Foundation from the year 2103 CE regarding SCP-4755.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>01/04/2010</td>
<td>Apollyon completes a manifestation event and exits the local timeline.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>4/17/2011</td>
<td><a href="/scp-4518">SCP-4518</a> is contained with significant effort.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>August 2012</td>
<td>Rainer Miller is contained as <a href="/scp-4051">SCP-4051</a> after covertly operating as a vigilante for several months.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>08/17/2012</td>
<td>Testing on SCP-4051 results in Dr. Anthony Roswell entering a coma and Dr. David Edwards become project lead over SCP-4051.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>08/31/2012</td>
<td>Procedure 350-PROMETHEAN is initiated for the first time on SCP-4051.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>07/18/2013</td>
<td>SCP-4051 is reclassified as Keter after <a href="/the-beast-beneath-the-library">a botched containment mission</a>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>09/08/2015</td>
<td><a href="/scp-4175">Alex Conrad</a> is neutralized.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>02/13/2016</td>
<td>Foundation Administrator Ethan Horowitz becomes the heir to SCP-4260 in order to prevent a ΩK-Class (&quot;End-of-Death&quot;) Scenario.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>2019</td>
<td>Edwina Drake is contained as <a href="/scp-4855">SCP-4855</a> after the propagation of a lethal cognitohazard destroys her hometown.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>07/26/2022</td>
<td>A Snap Back Scenario resulting from SCP-4855's clinical death occurs.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>2103</td>
<td>The Foundation ascends to a Tier V conceptual anomaly, becoming SCP-4755.</td>
</tr>
</table>
